  "prompt": "When is the best time to visit Singapore?",
  "response": "The best time to visit Singapore is generally between February and April. During these months, the weather is relatively dry, and you can expect less rainfall compared to other times of the year. Singapore has a tropical rainforest climate with consistent temperatures around 25-32\u00b0C (77-90\u00b0F) year-round. This period often has more sunshine and is ideal for outdoor activities and sightseeing. \n\nHowever, it's also worth noting that Singapore is a year-round destination due to its constant warm climate and numerous indoor attractions. The city-state hosts various festivals and events throughout the year, so you might want to plan your visit around specific happenings such as the Singapore Food Festival in July, the Singapore International Festival of Arts in May, or the festive light-ups during Christmas and the New Year celebrations.\n\nKeep in mind that hotel rates and airfares can be higher during peak seasons and major holidays, so it's advisable to book in advance for better deals.",
